================================================================================
PART 2 — CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 (for the ArUco marker generation components)
================================================================================

The ArUco marker generation features — specifically:

  • the JavaScript array `_ARUCO_N_TO_RAW` (mapping of numbers 1..125 to 4×4
    raw bit patterns), located in `plan de classe.html`;
  • the `_ARUCO_OPTS` decoding table used to render those bit patterns as 6×6
    matrices with the standard ArUco border;
  • the printable marker layout (`printSalleArucoMarkers`, `printArucoMarkersByList`,
    `_buildArucoMarkerHTML`, and the associated `@media print` rules
    `#am-print`, `.am-page`, `.am-tile`, etc.);

are derived from QCMcam by Sébastien COGEZ — https://qcmcam.net —
and are distributed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-
ShareAlike 4.0 International License (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode

Summary of obligations for these components:

  • BY (Attribution) — You must give appropriate credit to Sébastien COGEZ,
    provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were made. The
    credit "Marqueurs ArUco — Sébastien COGEZ — CC BY-NC-SA" is preserved
    in the application UI (QCMCam tab, ArUco marker print pages, About
    dialog) and must remain present in any redistribution.
  • NC (NonCommercial) — You may not use these components for commercial
    purposes. Pedagogical use (free, in classrooms, by educators) is
    explicitly intended and allowed.
  • SA (ShareAlike) — If you remix, transform, or build upon these specific
    components, you must distribute your contributions under the same
    license as the original.

These obligations apply ONLY to the ArUco-related components listed above.
The rest of the application (placement, attendance, snapshots, tablets,
multi-room, AESH, etc.) remains under MIT License.

================================================================================
Why this dual licensing?
================================================================================

QCMcam is a free pedagogical tool distributed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. We
embed a local generator for its ArUco markers (so that teachers can print
only the markers they need for their salle, recto-verso, with our own
layout) — which makes the marker-generation code a derivative work of
QCMcam. Out of respect for Sébastien COGEZ's choice of license, we apply
CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 to those specific components, while keeping MIT for the
rest of the application to remain compatible with the broader open-source
ecosystem.

If you have questions or would like to use these components in a context
that is unclear under this licensing, please get in touch via the project
repository: https://github.com/Belenos-Toutatis/plan-de-classe
